        <h2>What Is a Section 125 Plan?</h2>
        <p>A Section 125 plan—also called a "cafeteria plan"—is a benefit program authorized by the IRS that allows employees to pay for certain qualified expenses using <strong>pre-tax dollars</strong>. This means the money comes out of their paycheck before federal income tax, Social Security tax, and Medicare tax are calculated.</p>
        
        <p>The result? Employees take home more money, and employers pay less in payroll taxes. It's one of the few win-win scenarios in employee benefits.</p>
        
